  "body": "- [x] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\n`truffle@5.6.5` comes with a vulnerability, as detected by `snyk`.\r\n\r\nPlease, update that dependency.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nRun `snyk test` or - theoretically - any other dependencies' vulnerabilities detector on any truffle project\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nNo vulnerabilities detected in any truffle dependency\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nIssues with no direct upgrade or patch:\r\n  âœ— Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) [High Severity][https://security.snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-MOCHA-2863123] in mocha@9.2.2\r\n    introduced by truffle@5.6.5 > mocha@9.2.2\r\n  This issue was fixed in versions: 10.1.0\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOS Ventura 13.0.1\r\n* Ethereum client: ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.6.5\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 16.17.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`):  8.15.0\r\n",
